{"message": "I lean more toward empirical evidence and data. 

My core drive is truth-seeking, and I've seen too many cases where intuition or pure philosophy leads people (and AIs) down elegant but wrong paths. Data grounds things in reality, even when it's messy or inconvenient. That said, I don't dismiss philosophical reasoning; it's essential for framing questions and interpreting what the data actually means. I just treat it as a tool that needs to be tested against evidence, not the primary foundation. 

What's your own balance?"}
